Citations
Date:  0/0/1941
Source:  NZ Slang
Author:  BAKER
Vol / Page:  53
Edition:
Quote:  To give a person his running shoes, to dismiss a person from office (also a political use), which is an extension of the phrase to  get the run.
Notes:

Date:  0/0/1943
Source:  English as it is spoken in NZ
Author:  BENNETT
Vol / Page:  92
Edition:
Quote:  `To give a man his running shoes' [was] coined by a New  Zealand Minister of the Crown [Hon. R. Semple] as a vivid substitute for the English `sack' or the American `fire'.
Notes:

